						<summary>

						<p>Pillar set up in front of the Vishṇu temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1506 (in words) Tāraṇa, Śaradṛitu, Kārttīka ba. 11, Thursday</hi> corresponding to 1584 A.D., November, 19. However, the week day is not Thursday, it is Wednesday.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It gives the genealogy of the minister Anantaprabhu and records the establishment of an <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> named Laksmīnṛisiṁhapura, by him and his wife Timmāmbā.</p>						

						</summary>
